What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: There is actually a lot of work. You will be assigned a paper and while you work on that, there will be other assignments.
It's an awesome class. If you are interested in sports you will definitely enjoy it.
It is not an easy class and its a lot of work. But if you do it conscientiously you will definitely feel an improvement.
It is a good class for what it tries to do, but I would recommend taking 120 instead if your goal is to become a better writer. I learned some about researching, but not much else
I would definitely recommend this course to a fellow student. Not only did I improve immensly as a writer, but also enjoyed my time in class each day. Although it was a lot of work I liked doing it.

If you'r taking 114 take it with Mr. Gibbons. He is one of the best english teachers i have ever had. I grew tremendously over the semester as a writer. This was defiantly my favorite class all semester because class was most of the time funny and interesting
I would recommend it. It is necessary to learn how to be a college writer. There is a lot of writing and reading, but it is all worth it in the end.
The class is a lot of work, especially towards the beginning, but the topics are interesting and you improve as a writer.
I recommend this class to anyone who is interested in improving their writing skills.
Definitely recommend taking this course, it helped a lot with my writing
